SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYTuesday 19 April S10 V1 There is an important clash for both Reds at Anfield on Tuesday as Liverpool chase the title and Manchester United a Champions League spot. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Real Mallorca vs Deportivo Alaves: Mallorca have lost eight of their last nine outings. Alaves are four points behind them and sitting second from bottom in LaLiga.M2 Randers vs Silkeborg: Randers have lost their last two games, conceding three goals in each game. Silkeborg upset leaders FC Copenhagen in their last outing.M3 Burton Albion vs Rotherham United: Burton’s last three outings have all ended in goalless draws. Rotherham are second in League One but ahead of MK Dons on goal difference only.M4 Cambridge United vs Charlton Athletic: Charlton’s 2-0 home victory over Cambridge in December was the only previous meeting between the two clubsM5 Ipswich Town vs Wigan Athletic: Ipswich have won one of their past six outings. Wigan have a four point lead at the top of League One but lost at home at the weekend.M6 Oxford United vs Milton Keynes Dons: Oxford were away winners at the weekend while MK Dons suffered a surprise home reversal in their promotion bid.M7 Inter Milan vs AC Milan: This is the second leg of the Coppa Italia semi-final after the first leg last month ended goalless.M8 Liverpool vs Manchester United: Liverpool will go top of the Premier League if they win this clash against their old rivals. Both clubs were 3-2 winners on Saturday.M9 Real Betis vs Elche: Betis are unbeaten in their last six games and still chasing a place in next season’s Champions League. Elche won 3-0 at home on Saturday to Mallorca.M10 Villarreal vs Valencia: The last six clashes between these clubs have all been home victories. Suggested permutation:R16.00 1 x 1,2 x 3 x 1 x 2,3 x 2,3 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1